  "body" : "<p>Looking at the Android tutorials such as <a href=\"http://developer.android.com/resources/tutorials/notepad/notepad-ex1.html\">the Notepad tutorial</a>, I noticed that almost all variables are named starting with the letter 'm'. What convention is this, and where does it originate from?</p>\n"
